  abstract = {{The effects of increasing periods of mechanical cultivation on soil
   properties under maize and cassava are compared with those under savanna
   in south-western Nigeria. Bulk density is significantly greater under
   cultivation and total porosity, pH, organic matter and extractable
   nutrients are all significantly less than under savanna. However, the
   amounts of nitrate-nitrogen and extractable nutrients do not show clear
